The paper discusses the use of wireless communication in Network-on-Chip (NoC) systems, which is a topic related to embedded systems (cs.ET) and computer architecture (cs.AR). The paper also discusses the performance and cost trends of Analog-to-Digital Converters (ADCs), which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and electromagnetics (cs.EM). Finally, the paper discusses the scalability limitations of current NoCs and the potential for novel interconnect technologies, which is a topic related to network engineering (cs.NE).
